## 2. Security Enhancements Implemented
> [!NOTE]
> All changes are committed to your codebase via `server.js`, `page.js`, and the socket handlers.

### Backend Hardening
*   **Helmet.js Integration:** Automatically configures industry-standard HTTP security headers.
*   **Strict CORS:** Now rigorously structured to accept only matching origins `FRONTEND_URL` without loose wildcards.
*   **TURN API Endpoint (`/api/turn`):** We developed an endpoint leveraging Node's built-in `crypto` library. It hashes time-limited (`TTL` parameter based) ICE credentials so users don't have infinite access to your TURN relays. Only requests holding a valid JWT receive an ICE array.

### Socket Protection
*   **Session Throttling & Limiter:** Socket connections pass through a localized rate limiter map that forces a temporary block (`applyRateLimit`) if a client exceeds normal event thresholds.
*   **Single Device Locks:** Using an active tracking map, a user is prohibited from opening overlapping tabs and spamming the matchmaking queue under the same token.
*   **XSS Stripping:** We integrated `xss` library to purge malicious JS tags (`<script>`) from any plain text transmitted inside WebRTC signaling via `handleSignaling`. 

### Frontend Cleanup
*   **Zero-Credentials Client:** Removed all hardcoded ICE/STUN configurations situated freely inside `page.js`.
*   **Dynamic Binding:** The module fetches dynamic secrets safely per-load, blocking scraping utilities.

### Supabase Defenses
* Created the necessary `supabase_rls_policies.sql` artifact. These represent Row-Level Security definitions that guarantee row-level data segregation if a client interface directly hooks to the tables.

